<dashboard version="1.1" script="landing.js,aiqa_i18n_dom.js" hideEdit="true">
    <label>AI Query Assistant for Splunk</label>

    <!--
      Issue #26: in-panel headings demoted by one level (h1->h2, h2->h3) so
      they don't compete with the dashboard's own <h1> page label and the
      document outline stays valid.

      Issue #27: user-visible inline strings are wrapped in
      <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="..."> markers so a small DOM
      hook (appserver/static/aiqa_i18n_dom.js) can swap them via
      mcpUtils.t(key) at page load. The default-language English text is
      kept inline so the page still renders if JS is disabled or a key is
      missing from the dictionary.
    -->

    <row>
        <panel>
            <html>

            <div id="license_warning" style="display:none; background:#fff3cd; border:1px solid #ffc107; padding:15px; margin-bottom:20px; border-radius:4px;">
                <h3 style="color:#856404; margin-top:0;"><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.license.warningTitle">&#9888;&#65039; License Not Activated</span></h3>
                <p style="color:#856404; margin-bottom:10px;">
                    <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.license.warningBody">To use AI Query Assistant for Splunk, you need to activate your license first.</span>
                </p>
                <a href="license_activation" class="btn btn-primary"><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.license.activateNow">Activate License Now</span></a>
            </div>

            <h2 style="font-size:20px;"><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.overview.title">Overview</span></h2>
            <p>
            <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.overview.p1">AI Query Assistant for Splunk is an AI-powered Splunk application that enables users to query Splunk data using natural language.</span>
            </p>
            <p>
            <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.overview.p2">The app helps transform plain-language questions into structured SPL searches with intelligent assistance, improving query efficiency, usability, and analyst productivity. It supports multiple AI providers and includes layered security guardrails to help ensure safe and controlled usage in enterprise environments.</span>
            </p>
            <p>
            <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.overview.p3">All Python components in this app are fully compatible with Python 3.</span>
            </p>

            <hr/>
            <h2 style="font-size:20px;"><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.title">Quick Start</span></h2>

            <ol>
            <li><strong><a href="license_activation"><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.step1.link">Activate your license</span></a></strong> <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.step1.text">to enable the application.</span></li>
            <li><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.step2.prefix">Go to</span> <strong><a href="setup_page"><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.step2.link">Setup</span></a></strong> <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.step2.text">to configure your AI provider API credentials.</span></li>
            <li><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.step3.prefix">Go to</span> <strong><a href="mcp_providers"><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.step3.link">AI Providers</span></a></strong> <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.step3.text">to add and manage available AI models and endpoints.</span></li>
            <li><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.step4.prefix">Open</span> <strong><a href="mcp_query"><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.step4.link">Smart Query</span></a></strong> <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.quickstart.step4.text">to start querying Splunk using natural language.</span></li>
            </ol>

            <hr/>
            <h2 style="font-size:20px;"><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.title">Key Features</span></h2>

            <h3><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.nl2spl.title">Natural Language to SPL</span></h3>
            <p>
            <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.nl2spl.body">Convert plain-language questions into Splunk Processing Language (SPL) searches, making data exploration faster and more accessible.</span>
            </p>

            <h3><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.multi.title">Multi-Provider AI Support</span></h3>
            <p>
            <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.multi.body">Support for multiple AI providers, including:</span>
            </p>
            <ul>
            <li><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.multi.item1">OpenAI-compatible APIs</span></li>
            <li><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.multi.item2">Anthropic Claude</span></li>
            <li><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.multi.item3">Other compatible enterprise AI endpoints such as Doubao, DeepSeek, and Qwen</span></li>
            </ul>

            <h3><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.security.title">Security Guardrails</span></h3>
            <p>
            <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.security.body">Built-in multi-layer security controls help reduce operational risk by:</span>
            </p>
            <ul>
            <li><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.security.item1">Blocking potentially dangerous commands</span></li>
            <li><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.security.item2">Validating query time ranges</span></li>
            <li><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.security.item3">Filtering sensitive or restricted data patterns</span></li>
            <li><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.security.item4">Enforcing safer query generation behavior</span></li>
            </ul>

            <h3><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.history.title">Query History</span></h3>
            <p>
            <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.history.body">Track, review, and audit previous natural language queries and generated SPL results.</span>
            </p>

            <h3><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.templates.title">Query Templates</span></h3>
            <p>
            <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.features.templates.body">Save and reuse frequently used query patterns to improve consistency and operational efficiency.</span>
            </p>

            <hr/>
            <h2 style="font-size:20px;"><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.developer.title">Developer</span></h2>

            <p>
            <span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.developer.body">This app is built and maintained by</span> <a href="https://reallysec.com" target="_blank"><strong><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.developer.company">Anhui Reallysec Information Technology Co., Ltd.</span></strong></a><span class="aiqa-i18n" data-key="landing.developer.suffix"></span>
            </p>


            </html>
        </panel>
    </row>
</dashboard>
